	   <tr><td colspan=2>Speaking as a Wizard,<br><br>Ive read all these posts and there doesnt seem to be a Wizard, or at least one who knows the first thing about raiding, posting here.<br><br>As a Wizard use this robe would decrease downtime while soloing for sure, espeacialy with epic effect..I dont know how many of you are familiar with high end wizards, but Ive spent the better part of 10 minutes regening a blown mana bar. And Wizaards being the only int class that doesnt have some type mana regen ability, this is quite nice.<br><br>As far as endgame raids go, the uses are limited, but very worthwhile. First of all, you do not under any circumstance cast mana conversion or Barrier of Force during a fight, for two reasons.<br>One, in many Velios encounters large mobs have the nastiest AE's and they use them frequently, the only thing separating a useful nuking wizard from a dead one..are hitpoints, Because believe me the clerics arent worried about your skinny ass when Aayonar and his pets are silencing healers mana while beating the crap out their only line of defense. Second and this really makes it all a moot point, Barrier of Force is about the fastest way to piss off a mob. I dont care how long how many tanks have been beating it down or how many healers they had, you cast BoF and you become target #1. <br><br>The best use of the mana robe for wizard in a raid, is to use it between the fights and make sure your ready for the next one. Because Velios raids are nothing like the &quot;zone-some bad guys-Boss fight&quot; that many poeple are used to. <br>When you go into North Temple of Veeshan be prepared to spend 2 or 3 real life DAYS killing stuff that would make Venril Sathir piss himself.<br>An epic enhanced Wizard with a mana-robe makes these adventures easier on his guild by using his med-time (which isnt much) to robe down and be ready to blast the next mob, which could be only 30 seconds away.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
